kodkod.ast.visitor
Class DepthFirstReplacer

java.lang.Object
  kodkod.ast.visitor.DepthFirstReplacer
All Implemented Interfaces:
ReturnVisitor<Expression,Formula,Decls>
public abstract class DepthFirstReplacer
extends java.lang.Object
implements ReturnVisitor<Expression,Formula,Decls>

A depth first replacer. The default implementation returns the tree to which it is applied. Reference equality is used to determine if two nodes are the same. Subclasses may choose to cache replacements for certain nodes by properly implementing the lookup and cache methods. The default implementation does not perform any caching.

Author:
Emina Torlak
specfield:
cache: Node lone->lone Node

Method Detail

lookup

protected <N extends Node> N lookup(N node)
If the given node has already been visited and its replacement cached, the cached value is returned. Otherwise, null is returned. The default implementation does not perform any caching so this method simply returns null.

Returns:
this.cache[node]

cache

protected <N extends Node> N cache(N node,
                                   N replacement)
Caches the given replacement for the specified node, if this is a caching visitor. Otherwise does nothing. The method returns the replacement node. The default implemention just returns the replacement node.

Returns:
replacement
effects:
this.cache' = this.cache ++ node->replacement || this.cache' = this.cache
